      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, yeah. I mentioned this in an email to Ethan:\n\"If/when we do get the jit working, I\u0027d be tempted to go even further and remove more of the optimizations in the interpreter that cost us code size -- shrink the default vector width, some of the vectorized instructions for 2/3/4 component ops, threaded code (not sure if that one actually costs us, though - and it\u0027s probably a bigger bang for the buck than some of the others).\"\n\nI would like to do some experiments to figure out the answer on this one in particular (as there\u0027s a lot of boilerplate to support it).",
