      "writtenOn": "2020-04-02T18:14:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I ran through various benchmarks that exercise the interpreter (sksl_interp... and runtime...). The speedup ((Base - Threaded) / Base) was anywhere from 5 - 13%.\n\nI\u0027m not seeing a code size impact on flutter, which may be because they didn\u0027t have the interpreter compiled in at the time we switched things over. I did do release builds locally with and without threaded code, and looked at the change in the size of .text in SkSLByteCode.obj: Turning it on adds about 10.5 KB (46,408 -\u003e 57,357).",
